Description
Do you like making people smile?
IKEA offers an exciting and empowering work environment in a global marketplace. And as the world’s leader in life at home, you have exceptional opportunities to grow and develop together with us.
ABOUT THE JOB
A key part of this role will include serving our world famous hotdog, self-serve ice-cream cones and other yummy snacks. The roles will also support our Swedish Food Market, which sells a little taste of Sweden for our customers to take home.
Job Description :
Preparing and serving the highest quality food to both our customers and co-workers Being an advocate for our customers as you focus on ensuring they have a pleasurable and memorable shopping experience Having an energetic and team focused approach as this is one department that can get seriously busy Being passionate about our Bistro & Swedish Food Market products with a genuine interest and enthusiasm to learn about our business and build a broad variety of capabilities Having a strong desire to pursue a career with endless possibilities and work in a fun, fast-paced and dynamic environment Providing support to fellow co-workers as well as the Bistro & Swedish Food Market Team Leader & Manager
Requirements
Having a minimum 2-3 years of experience in a retail industry or fast food restaurant Must be computer literate Able to perform inventory/stock checking
Have good communication skills and service-oriented Have good personal discipline, a flexible approach to work and enjoy change You are hands on and able to work in a fast paced environment Must be able to work in shifts and committed to working on weekends and public holidays
All applications will be treated confidentially & only short listed candidates will be notified
Please click "Apply Now" button to apply
